SECTION 5: TWO PREDICTIONS COMPARED
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  The CD framework makes two predictions from unification:

  1. sin2_tW from alpha_EM + alpha_s (PHYS-27):
     Predicted: 0.22845 (no threshold)
     Measured:  0.23122
     Miss: 1.2%%

  2. alpha_s from alpha_EM + sin2_tW (this paper):
       Predicted (dimensionless)           0.00082756037156
       Measured (dimensionless)            0.118
       Miss (%%)                           99.298677651

  Both predictions use two of the three couplings as input
  and predict the third. Both miss by ~1-2%% at one loop.
  Both are expected to improve at two loops.

SECTION 6: PARAMETER COUNT IMPLICATIONS
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  If unification is exact (Delta = 0), the three couplings
  alpha_EM, sin2_tW, alpha_s are related by the unification
  condition. Only TWO are independent. The third is derived.

  Combined with theta_QCD = 0 (PHYS-7) and the Koide
  conditional (m_tau from K=2/3), the parameter reductions:

    theta_QCD = 0:  19 -> 18  (energy minimization)
    m_tau:          18 -> 17  (Koide conditional on a^2=2)
    alpha_s:        17 -> 16  (unification condition)
    sin2_tW:        (redundant with alpha_s — same condition)

  The unification condition reduces by 1, not 2, because
  it relates three couplings with one condition. Either
  alpha_s or sin2_tW is derived, not both independently.

